pan class=title> xp res in zone.</span><hr size=1> Last night i wanted to buy something and the person wouldn't give me a price.<br>
<br>
I was ask 'Do you charge for xp res?'<br>
<br>
i honestly told her, I don't set a price, but I do accept donations.  (but i got the impression my price was going to be based on weather or not i took anything for xp res.)<br>
<br>
I hadn't never thought about it before that.  Normally i get a tell from someone and they ask me if i could xp res, i normally ask them to drag the corpse to me.  I never set a price or anything.  If they offer me something i accept it but i don't put a price on it.<br>
<br>
I won't res someone if it would put my group in any danger, example we are chain pulling and i am LoM  I just tell them that i don't have the mana to do it atm and to ask someone else.<br>
But if i am with a good group with enchanter/bard and i have extra mana I will res them near my group.<br>
<br>
I don't think i am a greedy person, any donation i get would go toward my equipment of gems for symbol spells.<br>
<br>
Plus before i log off for the night, i general shout to the zone, oftering free 50 percent res is anyone needs before i log.<br>
I try to be helpful, trying to earn a good repution in game.  I know most of the ppl have play much longer then i have.<br>
<br>
Example, last night a guy ask me if i would res one of his group members, he brought me the corpse.  I ressed it, he gave me 30pp, that is more then i normally get in 2 hours.<br>
<br>
A few hours later, he ask me if i would res him.  I brought me the corpse, he oftered me 30 more and i canceled the trade.  Healed him up then buffed him and wished him well.<br>
<br>
So i do some free xp res's but also accept donations.<br>
<br>
I think i am well known in DL now, I seem to have a rep for keeping rangers alive.<br>
 <p>45th lvl High Elven Cleric of Tunare<br>
